“While 300,000 species of plant have edible parts , just 20 species account for 90% of the world’s food , and three –
wheat , maize and rice – supply more than half . To be so heavily reliant on a tiny handful of crops puts humanity in a
precarious position , ” writes Dimbleby . Our food system poses more immediate health threats , too . As the pandemic has
sadly highlighted , poor diet is a major factor in death and disease. Around 64,000 deaths every year in England can be
 attributed to poor diet , which costs the economy an estimated £74 billion – around £409 per person . The UK is now the
 third fattest country in the G7 .